<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Recall 07504 - AIR BRAKE TUBING on 4300 and 4400 tractors built 6/21/2004 thru 2/21/2007</stitle>
    <recall id="rec07504">
        <recallnumber>07504</recallnumber>
        <market>U.S., Export</market>
        <recalldate>March, 2007</recalldate>
        <subjectfile>BRAKES</subjectfile>
        <subject>AIR BRAKE TUBING on 4300 and 4400 tractors built 6/21/2004 thru 2/21/2007</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4300
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>06/21/2004</startdate>
                        <enddate>02/21/2007</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4400
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>06/21/2004</startdate>
                        <enddate>02/21/2007</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>04092</ucode>
                <ucode>04AZG</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <defect>
            <para>
                <exhotlnk document="../recalls/Rec07504.pdf" bookname="RECALL">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the dealer
                    letter
                </exhotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>Air brake tubing is routed incorrectly causing the rear axle of the tractor to not receive the proper
                air pressure while a trailer is connected to the vehicle. This reduced air pressure lessens the braking
                force the tractor's rear axle brakes can apply. Under certain loaded tractor-trailer conditions, this
                reduced braking force may increase stopping distance. An unexpected increase in stopping distance may
                contribute to a vehicle crash which may result in property damage, personal injury or death.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>MODELS INVOLVED</title>
            </para>
            <para>This Safety Recall involves certain 4300 and 4400 tractors built 6/21/2004 thru 2/21/2007 with feature
                codes:
                <emph type="bold">0004092</emph>
                - TRACTOR DUAL AIR BRAKE SYSTEM AND
                <emph type="bold">0004AZG</emph>
                - OMIT AIR BRAKE ANTILOCK SYSTEM.
            </para>
        </defect>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="7">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious eye injury, always wear safe eye protection when you perform vehicle
                        maintenance or service.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent unexpected movement of the vehicle and possible serious personal injury or death,
                        block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving in both directions.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the vehicle's air tanks by repeatedly depressing the brake pedal or opening the
                    tank drain valves.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open vehicle hood. Locate and remove the single 3/8" OD RED air brake tube located on
                    the bottom side of the TP-5 Tractor Protection Valve, mounted on the driver's side of the firewall.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install quick connect tee (2024458C1) into port where single 3/8" OD RED tube was
                    located.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750402" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the BP-1 Bobtail Proportioning valve on the rear frame cross member.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750403" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750403.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 1/8" NPT plug from BP1 valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750404" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean threads if necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install elbow (2017509C1). Orient fitting toward driver's side as shown.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750405" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 3/8" OD BLACK service tubing (417199C3) to connect BP-1 bobtail proportioning
                    valve with the TP-5 tractor protection valve. Route tubing as necessary securing with strap-locks no
                    greater than 12" (305mm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0750406" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6a - 3/8" OD Service Tube shown in RED for Clarity</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0750407" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0750407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6b - 3/8" OD Service Tube shown in RED for Clarity</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-fill vehicle air tanks. Ensure there are no air leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
